"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn documentation states that the rc argument in set_style() function can only override the parameters that are part of the style definition. However, 'grid.linewidth' is a matplotlib parameter that is not part of the style definition. It should be passed to the set_context() function or set_theme() function. But 'grid.linewidth' was passed to set_context() correctly in this code. The issue here is with set_style() function which is used correctly but set_context() should have been used for 'grid.linewidth'. However the actual issue here is sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict), it should be sns.set_context('notebook', rc=scale_dict) because set_context() requires the name of the context as the first argument.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n---\\n>scale_dict = {\\n6c6\\n---\\n>    'lines.linewidth': 4,\\n7c7\\n---\\n>    'grid.linewidth': 4\\n8c8\\n---\\n>sns.set_context('notebook', rc=scale_dict)\"\n}"